$interpreted: Tingko: Withering sickness!? Wasn't it cured!?
Doctor: Who said it was cured!? It was stable, temporarily! We haven't cured the root of the problem yet. Her qi is all out of balance.

Jiyanama: But there were hardly any signs of illness... 
How could it just flare up again so quickly?
Doctor: It seems to be her nature. She's impetuous. When symptoms worsen, her body will react by fainting.
Jihasaha: Just tell us how to cure it!
Doctor: Administer her medicine, same as before, and let her rest. She'll get better over time.
Jihasaha: I mean how do you get rid of it, so it never comes back!?
Tingko: Calm down...
Jihasaha: How could I be calm!? She's already got enough problems living here. Now she gets some incurable disease!?
Tingko: Jihasaha...
Doctor: Well... if we made a tonic from stonecrop, then there might be a chance to cure it at the root.
Jihasaha: Then go get some!
Doctor: That's impossible. Stonecrop only grows in xiong dens.
Tingko: Xiong!? Aren't those super deadly beasts!?
Doctor: Thats right, so we'll make do with the medicine we've got here. I'm not going to risk my life for a hostage.
Jiyanama: I guess we'll just have to settle for what we have.
Jihasaha: No! I'll go get it!
Tingko: Jihasaha, xiong are insanely dangerous! Plus, your injuries have only just been bandaged up!
Jihasaha: I can't sit around and watch her suffer.
Tingko: But, the princess ordered you...
Jihasaha: I've been helpless long enough. I'll ask for her forgiveness later, when she's better.
TIngko: Wait, I'll go with you!
Jihasaha: You!?
TIngko: It's my responsibility to watch you.
Jihasaha: Then let's go.
Tingko: You notice all those lookie-loos stopped following us a ways back? We must be getting into dangerous territory...
Jihasaha: Then be careful.
Tingko: I'm sorry for slowing you down. It's already dark and we still haven't found those herbs...
Jihasaha: Nothing to do with you. Xiong are just hard to find.
Tingko: Ohhh let me see that xiong xiong xiong~
Jihasaha: ...Are you singing a... xiong song?
Tingko: I just thought they might be sensitive to noise, you know... Maybe they'd come out?
Jihasaha: I'm tired. Let's take a rest and eat something.
Jihasaha: Here, have some. I've shared these with the princess, before, too.
Tingko: Thanks. Here, you can have some of what I brought.
TIngko: Ugh... it's hard to imagine the princess eating this...
Jihasaha: Food's food. It keeps you alive. The princess was never picky.
TIngko: ...Then what about mine? You like it?
Jihasaha: It is... adequate.
TIngko: I've made these for the princess before, too. She loved it!
Jihasaha: It's too sweet.
Tingko: I should teach you how to make some for the princess, as an apology.
Jihasaha: That's not really my style.

Tingko: Yeah... it's hard to imagine you in the kitchen... 
Eesh, kind of scary, actually...
Jihasaha: Maybe I could sing her a song.
Tingko: You...
Jihasaha: Quiet!
Tingko: Huh?
Jihasaha: There was a noise... a beast! There!
Tingko: That's the stonecrop, isn't it? But... so many xiong. What should we do?
Jihasaha: We've got to fight them!
Jihasaha: (Ugh... I can't see anything... this won't work...)
Jihasaha: (A light...! Great, I can see!)
Jihasaha: (This warm light... it's familiar...)
Jihasaha: (Thank you, Tingko.)
